# Delegate Self-Contained Tasks

If you won't reuse the context needed to complete a task in the main conversation, delegate it to a **fast subagent** and have it report back.

## When to delegate

- Creating files: rules, skills, scripts, configs, AGENTS.md, documentation
- Adding tools/features to existing code following established patterns
- Any task where you'd gather context, do the work, then move on

## When NOT to delegate

- You need the intermediate context to inform the next step in conversation
- The task is trivial (single edit, quick lookup)
- You're iterating with the user on the design (delegate the implementation once the design is settled)

## Prompt guidelines

- Tell the subagent to read existing files first for pattern/style consistency
- Specify exact file paths and whether to create or edit
- State what to return — concise confirmation, not the full content
- Include all necessary context since subagents have no access to the conversation
